{{about|the businessman|the ice hockey player|Alexander Frolov|the footballer|Aleksandr Frolov (footballer)}} {{Infobox person | image = <!-- Only freely-licensed images may be used to depict living people. See [[WP:NONFREE]]. --> | | image_size = 150px | | name = Aleksandr Frolov | caption = | birth_date = 17 May 1964 | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | other_names = | known_for = | occupation = CEO of [[Evraz]] | website = [http://www.evraz.com/about/management www.evraz.com] }}
'''Aleksandr Vladimirovich Frolov''' ({{lang-ru|Александр Владимирович Фролов}}) (born 17 May 1964) is the CEO of [[Evraz]], one of the largest [[steel]] producers. In 2013, the company became the largest Russian producer of coking coal. According to ''[[Forbes]]'' list of billionaires, he has a net worth of $2.4 billion as of March 2018. He ranks #1,161 on Forbes’ List of Billionaires.<ref name="Forbes">{{cite news | url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/alexander-frolov/?list=billionaires| title=The World's Billionaires: ''Alexander Frolov''| publisher=Forbes | author= | date=17 March 2015 | accessdate = 2015-03-17}}</ref>
==Career== Frolov graduated with honors from the [http://bio.fizteh.ru Department of Molecular and Chemical Physics] of the [[Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology]] in 1987.<ref>[http://bio.fizteh.ru/graduate/years/1987.html DMCP graduates]. Class of 1987</ref> He received his Ph.D. in physics and mathematics from the same institute in 1991. Frolov worked at the [[Kurchatov Institute]] of Atomic Energy in Moscow. In 1994 he became an entrepreneur. Since 2007 he has been the [[CEO]] of [[Evraz]] ([[London Stock Exchange|LSE]]: [https://web.archive.org/web/20080214122243/http://www.londonstockexchange.com/en-gb/pricesnews/prices/Trigger/genericsearch.htm?bsg=true EVR]). Frolov’s partner, [[Alexander Abramov]], is the Chairman of EVRAZ.<ref name="Forbes" />
==Personal life==
Frolov is married and has one child.<ref name="Forbes" />
==See also== *[[Evraz Group]] *[[Alexander Abramov]]
