'''Mieke Offeciers-Van De Wiele''' ([[Kruibeke]], 12 August 1952) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businesswoman and former Belgian minister. She is married to Erwin Offeciers.

She was head of the study department of the [[VOKA|VEV]] when in 1992 she became minister of budget for the CVP, but she returned within a year to the VEV as CEO. Between 2000 and 2004 she worked for KPMG and since 2004 she works for [[Interel]], a leading public affairs and strategic communications consulting firm. She was a member of the [[Coudenberg group]], a Belgian federalist [[think tank]].

