{{Expand Spanish|Ruy Barbosa Popolizio|date=July 2014}} '''Ruy Barbosa Popolizio''' (December 2, 1919 – June 8, 2014) was a [[Chile]]an [[businessman]], [[politician]], and [[oenologist]]. Barbosa served as the [[Ministry of Agriculture of Chile|Minister of Agriculture]] from September 26, 1963, until November 3, 1964, as well as the Minister of National Assets briefly from September to November 1963. He later became the dean of the [[University of Chile]] from 1968 until 1969.<ref name=uchile>{{cite news|first=|last=|title=La Universidad de Chile despide al ex rector Ruy Barbosa |url=http://www.uchile.cl/noticias/101964/la-universidad-de-chile-despide-al-ex-rector-ruy-barbosa |work=[[University of Chile]] |publisher= |date=2014-06-09 |accessdate=2014-07-06}}</ref>
Barbosa Popolizio died in [[Santiago, Chile]], on June 8, 2014, at the age of 94.<ref name=uchile/>
