{{Use British English|date=June 2018}} [[File:Ascential logo.jpg|thumb|right|300px|[[Ascential]] is the parent company of WGSN]] '''WGSN ''' (formerly World Global Style Network)<ref>Avery Trufelman, [http://99percentinvisible.org/episode/the-trend-forecast/ The Trend Forecast] 09.20.2016 </ref><ref>Emma Barnett, [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/mediatechnologyandtelecoms/8482964/Trend-spotting-is-the-new-36bn-growth-business.html Trend-spotting is the new £36bn growth business: With fortunes to be made in fickle businesses like fashion, trend forecasting is becoming increasingly important for creative industries.] ''[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]'', 1 May 2011</ref> is a [[trend forecasting]] company of [[parent organisation]] [[Ascential]]. WGSN was founded in 1998 in [[West London (sub region)|West London]] by brothers Julian and [[Marc Worth]].<ref>marcworth.co.uk [http://marcworth.co.uk/about-me/ About Me]</ref><ref>[https://www.facebook.com/pg/WGSNofficial/about/?ref=page_internal Facebook page]</ref> Emap (now [[Ascential]]), a [[business-to-business]] publisher and exhibitions company, bought the company in October 2005 for £140m.<ref>Jonathan Moules, [https://www.ft.com/content/b890964c-e39a-11e0-8990-00144feabdc0 My liquidity moment: Marc Worth] ''[[Financial Times]]'', SEPTEMBER 29, 2011 </ref>
==Recent history== In 2013, WGSN merged with its biggest competitor, Stylesight.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.drapersonline.com/news/best-of-wgsn-and-stylesight-to-be-combined-in-new-wgsncom-service/5062136.article|title=Best of WGSN and Stylesight to be combined in new WGSN.com service|work=Drapers|access-date=2017-03-22|language=en}}</ref> Like WGSN, Stylesight had a vast library of [[fashion forecasting]], trend information, archival photos, and even sketches and patterns for [[designer]]s to use. Keeping the WGSN name, the new product has been designed around the technology developed by Stylesight and launched in 2014.
In February 2016, [[Ascential|Ascential plc]], an international media company that includes WGSN in its portfolio, was the subject of an £800m [[initial public offering]].<ref>[http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/wgsn-appoints-kevin-silk-as-managing-director-300306886.html WGSN Appoints Kevin Silk As Managing Director] Aug 01, 2016.</ref>
In 2016, WGSN started a global series of summits known as WGSN Futures, with events in [[New York City]], [[London]], [[São Paulo]], [[Cape Town]], [[Melbourne]], [[Dubai]] and [[Hong Kong]].{{fact|date=March 2017}}
== Products == As an online service, the business derives its [[revenue]]s from six different product [[subscription]]s (WGSN Insight, WGSN Fashion, WGSN Lifestyle & Interiors, WGSN Barometer, WGSN Instock, WGSN Styletrial),<ref>[https://www.wgsn.com/en/products/insight/ WGSN Insight], [https://www.wgsn.com/en/products/fashion/ WGSN Fashion], [https://www.wgsn.com/en/products/lifestyle-interiors/ WGSN Lifestyle & Interiors], [https://www.wgsn.com/en/products/instock WGSN Instock], [https://www.wgsn.com/en/products/styletrial WGSN Styletrial]</ref> a custom advisory business (WGSN Mindset)<ref>[https://www.wgsn.com/en/products/mindset/ WGSN Mindset]</ref> and a global series of events (WGSN Futures).<ref>[https://www.wgsn.com/en/products/futures/ WGSN Futures]</ref>
Its trend forecasting service includes what's new and next in [[apparel]], [[beauty]], [[Color|colour]], [[marketing]], [[retail]] and [[wearables]].<ref>Hayley Tsukayama, [http://www.dailyherald.com/article/20170318/business/170318968/ What's next for wearables? Check out Google and Levi's smart jean jacket], ''[[The Washington Post]]'' 3/18/2017 </ref> The firm has predicted that the [[smartphone]] will be obsolete by 2030.<ref>observer.com [http://observer.com/2016/11/a-wgsn-forecaster-predicts-how-we-will-live-and-shop-in-2030/ An Expert Predicts How We Will Live and Shop in 2030], Dena Silver, 11/08/16</ref>
